result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyrone D Patterson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Tyrone D Patterson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Tyrone D Patterson was found guilty of Criminal Damage to Property [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tyrone D Patterson in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Defendant Tyrone D Patterson in custody.  Ryan T. Sanson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 23 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 23 days time served.  THIS IS A TIME SERVED DISPOSITION.  Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by the end of probation in 13CM3008.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
Branch 23, Judge Grady in trial, case spun to branch 40, Judge Dallet.

Defendant Tyrone D Patterson in court, in custody, with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Michael Davis Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
AS TO COUNT 4
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion from the state, the court ordered Count 4 Dismissed, But Read In.
AS TO COUNT 2
Defendant changes plea(s) to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea(s).  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record. Court advised defendant of penalties for violation of NO CONTACT ORDER. Court advised that under 48 USC Section 922(g)(9) the defendant is prohibited from possession of a firearm and/or ammunition after conviction of a misdemeanor crime of domestic violence.Case adjourned to branch 23 for Sentencing.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for September 3, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub in court, defendant Tyrone D Patterson not in court, in custody.  Michael Davis Thurston appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Jury Trial. 1st call. Defendant NOT produced.
AS TO COUNTS 1, 3, 5, 6, 7, 8 & 9
Case is set for Jury Trial. Defense ready to proceed. State's essential witness failed to appear.  State has no alternative theory of prosecution. Defense motion to Dismiss is GRANTED by the Court without prejudice.
